It’s understood the men were working at a construction site at the time of the collapse on Monday afternoon. JOHANNESBURG - Three construction workers have died and one sustained critical injuries following a structural collapse in Isipingo south of Durban. It’s understood the men were working at a construction site at the time of the collapse on Monday afternoon. Rescue Care's Garrith Jamieson said the workers were stuck under rubble: “A wall had collapsed on to four construction workers who were working at the time. Unfortunately, three sustained severe medical injuries and there was nothing paramedics could do for them and were declared deceased on the scene.”